&lt;p&gt;You will be the first point of contact for GoCardless users and partners, resolving their queries, improving their onboarding experience, and helping them to navigate the GoCardless product. You’ll also be verifying new accounts to ensure they meet the guidelines and are able to transact safely on the GoCardless platform.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be speaking to English-speaking clients on a daily basis through emails, chats and phone calls. You’ll also be collaborating with internal teams such as Payment Operations, Engineering, Customer Success, and more…&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In doing this role, you’ll develop a thorough understanding of financial services, particularly in bank payments, direct debit, and open banking. Here, you will have the opportunity to grow with a business that’s looking to pioneer a new age of payments.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We work with tools such as Zendesk, Slack, Jira, and more, so if you’re familiar with those - you’ll be ready and set.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to fill roles in shifts:&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1) Rotation Shift:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working through 4 days (4 days working, 4 days off, etc), 8 am - 8 pm, after probation, working in a hybrid way&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;2)&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Regular Shift:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Monday through Friday, working time changing every week (8 am - 5 pm; 9 am - 6 pm; 10 am - 7 pm), working in a hybrid way&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Probation Time&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;2 months, Monday - Friday, 10 am - 7 pm, onsite&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
